              <figcaption class="image-gallery__slide-caption text-gray-700 text-center text-sm pt-8 md:pt-10">Jailimar Laverde, 17, (left) and Yanny Trejo, 19, (right) wait in a queue of hundreds of people outside a supermarket in Caracas rumored to have received a shipment of corn flour and butter, March 19, 2016. Both teenagers said they got pregnant because they could no longer find birth control pills in Venezuela.&nbsp;
